CERADYNE POSTS $198,000 PROFIT FOR 2ND QUARTER 
Ceradyne Inc., the Costa Mesa-based manufacturer of industrial ceramics, posted 
net income of $198,000 for the 1990 second quarter, contrasted with a loss of 
$1.4 million for the quarter in 1989. 
Sales increased 7%, to $6.1 million from $5.7 million. 
For the first half, the company reported a net profit of $264,000, contrasted 
with a net loss of $2.3 million for the first six months of 1989. Sales were up 
3%, to $12.1 million from $11.7 million. 
The company said its recovery plan emphasizing cost reductions and operating 
controls was primarily responsible for the favorable results. 
